1) The catalogs I have are stored here:
    /global/cscratch1/sd/avariu/desi/ABACUS_2GPC
    /global/cscratch1/sd/avariu/desi/UNIT_3GPC/sv3_v1.0_mycosmo/h5py/

2) Prepare mocks into a format that can be interpreted by fiber assigment, unifying QSO, ELG and LRGs (dark time)
>> prepare_files_SV3-UNITmocks_fromhdf5.py 
OUTPUTFILE = 'targets-UNIT-mtlz_SV3_alltracers_sv3bits_v2.fits'

3) Run fba_run in mocks:
fba_run --targets /global/cscratch1/sd/acarnero/fiberassign/targets-UNIT-mtlz_SV3_alltracers_sv3bits_v2.fits --sky /global/cfs/cdirs/desi/survey/catalogs/SV3/LSS/skies.fits --footprint /global/cfs/cdirs/desi/survey/catalogs/SV3/LSS/tiles-DARK.fits --dir fiberassigment --prefix mocks

4) RuNING mkCAT
>> python mkMock_SV3.py --type dark --verspec mock --cuttar y --mockmtl y

5) Finally, run for LRG as:
python mkMock_SV3.py --type LRG --verspec mock --combd n --fulld y --clus y 


----------------

For randoms:

2) Prepare randoms for fiber assigment (we will only use FAVAIL, therefore, it doesnt matter if they are together or not):
>> python prepare_files_SV3-UNITmocks_fromhdf5_randoms.py 
OUTPUTFILE = 'targets-UNIT-mtlz_SV3_alltracers_sv3bits_v2_random1.fits'

3) Run fba_run in randoms:
fba_run --targets /global/cscratch1/sd/acarnero/fiberassign/targets-UNIT-mtlz_SV3_alltracers_sv3bits_v2_random1.fits --sky /global/cfs/cdirs/desi/survey/catalogs/SV3/LSS/skies.fits --footprint /global/cfs/cdirs/desi/survey/catalogs/SV3/LSS/tiles-DARK.fits --dir fba_random1 --prefix ran1

4) RuNING mkCAT
>> python mkMock_SV3_randoms.py --type dark --verspec mock --combr y --cutran y --ranmtl y

5) Finally, for the LRG as:
>> python mkMock_SV3_randoms.py --type LRG --verspec mock --fullr y --clusran y

